The Writeback feature in Inforiver visuals provides you the ability to send data and formatting configuration from Inforiver to a Web URL.
The data is exported in a `.csv` format.

<div class="center">
    <Zoom>
        <img src={useBaseUrl('img/writeback-arch.png')}/>
    </Zoom>
        <p>Writeback Architecture</p>
</div>

## Configure Writeback in Inforiver

* In Power BI Desktop, select the **Visualizations** pane on the right-hand side.
* From the **Format** section, Select **Writeback**.
* Turn on the **On** toggle to enable writeback feature.

<div style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>
    <Zoom>
    <img
    height="650"
    src={useBaseUrl('img/writeback-on.png')}
    />
    </Zoom>
    <div class="center"><p>Enable writeback</p></div>
</div>

* In the **Writeback URL** box, enter URL of the backend data source to which Inforiver will post the data.

## Performing Writeback

* Select the **Export** tab from the top ribbon bar.
* Select **Writeback**.

<div class="center">
    <Zoom>
    <img
    alt="Writeback icon"
    src={useBaseUrl('img/writeback-enabled.png')}
    />
    </Zoom>
</div>

* Once the data is posted to the backend URL, a success message is displayed:

<div class="center">
    <Zoom>
    <img
    alt="Writeback success"
    src={useBaseUrl('img/writeback-success.png')}
    />
    </Zoom>
</div>
